Biography

2007 - JUNIOR SEASON: Injury ended season after the first two games. Still placed fourth on the team in rushing with 92 ground yards. Rushed for 45 yards on 20 carries at Albany State (Aug. 25) and 47 yards on 8 runs versus Fayetteville State (Sept. 2). 2006 - SOPHOMORE SEASON: Placed second on the team in rushing with 454 yards. Tied for team lead with six rushing touchdowns. Led the Eagles in rushing for five consecutive games from Sept. 30 to Oct. 28. Rushed for a season-best 84 yards and a score on 17 carries at Fayetteville State (Oct. 14). Ran for 83 yards and two touchdowns on 11 attempts versus Johnson C. Smith (Nov. 4). Amassed season-high 96 all-purpose yards at Bowie State (Sept. 30) with 73 rushing yards, 18 kickoff return yards and 5 punt return yards. 2005 - FRESHMAN SEASON: Fourth-leading rusher for the Eagles as a rookie with 165 yards on 31 attempts. Averaged 5.3 yards per carry. Returned two kickoffs for 86 yards (43.0 avg.), including a 78-yard touchdown return against Livingstone (Oct. 22), which resulted in the CIAA Special Teams Player of the Week award. Amassed season-best 129 all-purpose yards (51 rush, 78 kickoff return) versus Livingstone (Oct. 22). Rushed for a season-high 53 yards on 11 carries in first college game against Edward Waters (Aug. 27). QUINCE ORCHARD HIGH SCHOOL: PERSONAL: Born July 4, 1985, in Gaithersburg, Maryland. Parents are Jeff Toliver, Jr. and Sharon Anderson. Business Management major at NCCU.
